<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-21953] camel-groovy: GroovyLanguage.stop may throw UnsupportedOperationException</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-21953</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;GroovyLanguage.stop attempts to clear its script cache:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/camel/blob/80ee23a2bc408ae959664f240ee63edac5248723/components/camel-groovy/src/main/java/org/apache/camel/language/groovy/GroovyLanguage.java#L86&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/camel/blob/80ee23a2bc408ae959664f240ee63edac5248723/components/camel-groovy/src/main/java/org/apache/camel/language/groovy/GroovyLanguage.java#L86&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, if the builder was used to configure GroovyLanguage, the cache will be an unmodifiable Map. Which causes an UnsupportedOperationException when .clear() is invoked.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/camel/blob/80ee23a2bc408ae959664f240ee63edac5248723/components/camel-groovy/src/main/java/org/apache/camel/language/groovy/GroovyLanguage.java#L194-L204&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/camel/blob/80ee23a2bc408ae959664f240ee63edac5248723/components/camel-groovy/src/main/java/org/apache/camel/language/groovy/GroovyLanguage.java#L194-L204&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
